# Cloudflare Pages headers stub - inert on GitHub Pages.
#
# GitHub Pages ignores this file. It is shipped now so that a future migration
# to Cloudflare Pages (or fronting the apex with a Cloudflare Worker) lands
# the full Zero-Trust HTTP-header set without a second source change.
#
# Background: audit/11_spa_structural_audit.md spa-S2 / S4 / S5 cannot be
# expressed as <meta http-equiv> tags (X-Content-Type-Options is partial,
# frame-ancestors and Permissions-Policy are HTTP-only). Once headers can
# be set at the boundary, the meta CSP in web/templates/base.html should be
# removed in favor of the policy below (one source of truth).
#
# References:
#   audit/11_spa_structural_audit.md
#   https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# To activate:
#   1. Configure Cloudflare Pages with publish directory = docs/
#   2. Either move this file to docs/_headers, or update web/build.py to
#      copy it there as part of the build (suggested: alongside the
#      shutil.copytree(STATIC_DIR, ...) call at build.py:1728).
#   3. Drop the <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"> from base.html
#      and the <meta name="referrer"> tag (both are now HTTP-side).

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; img-src 'self' data: https://*.tile.openstreetmap.org https://server.arcgisonline.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://giscus.app; connect-src 'self' https://giscus.app; frame-src https://giscus.app; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin

# Photos and static assets are public records intentionally served with
# permissive CORS so syndication tools can fetch them. Inmate photos are
# public under ORC 149.43; data files (search.json, dispatches.json, RSS)
# are licensed CC BY-NC 4.0 per audit/00_index.md and the data page footer.
/photos/*
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

/static/*
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/feed.xml
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300
/booked.xml
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300
/released.xml
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300

# Search and dispatch JSON used by the homepage; same caching as RSS.
/search.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300
/dispatches.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300
